Social media companies partnering with health authorities to combat misinformation on coronavirus Social networks step up strategy for combatting COVID-19 misinformation.
The World Health Organization thinks so.
"We're focused on making sure everyone can access credible and accurate information," Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg said in a statement this week.
"If you search for coronavirus on Facebook, you'll see a pop-up that directs you to the World Health Organization or your local health authority for the latest information."
"In each country where we have launched the initiative, we have partnered with the national public health agency or the World Health Organization (@WHO) directly."